metatags.og:description:
> Swiftype [https://swiftype.com/], a Y Combinator startup that creates search
engines for websites, has raised $1.7 million in seed funding from Andreessen
Horowitz, NEA, Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, Ignition and several angel
investors.

Founded in 2012 [http://techcrunch.com/2012/05/08/swiftype-launch/], Swiftype
builds search engines in real time, organizing pages based on importance
